claim.claim-text:
Device according to claim 13, wherein the insertion means comprises:
- a skin attachment surface coated with an adhesive layer for securing attachment to the skin and having holes or recesses allowing the passage of the electrodes;
- a spring-type retraction mechanism of the skin attachment surface pulling the skin attachment surface together with the attached skin towards the tip of the electrodes;
- withholding means keeping the retraction mechanism pre-stressed in the ready-to-use position such that the tip of the electrodes is concealed by the skin attachment surface and prevented to contact the skin;
- a release and actuation element releasing the blockage of the retraction mechanism by the withholding means and actuating skin insertion of the electrodes by the relaxation of the retraction mechanism pulling the skin attached to the skin attachment surface against the tip of the electrodes, and actuating the control elements.
